---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms | Mod Labs"
  description="Terms of service for using the Mod Labs website and requesting modding or repair work."
>
  <section class="hero-gradient border-bottom border-brand py-5">
    <div class="container" data-aos="fade-up">
      <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold section-title mb-2">Terms</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-brand lead mb-0">Starter terms — have a lawyer review before going live.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8 text-muted-brand" data-aos="fade-up">
          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Services</h2>
          <p>
            Mod Labs provides modding and repair services as described on this site. Pricing on the Services page is informational until confirmed after intake. Complex damage, prior rework, or missing parts may change scope and cost.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Shipping &amp; risk</h2>
          <p>
            For mail-in work, you are responsible for packing and insuring shipments. Risk of loss in transit rests with the carrier and chosen insurance unless otherwise agreed in writing.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Warranty</h2>
          <p>
            Any workmanship warranty will be communicated with your invoice or completion notice. Abuse, firmware changes by others, or physical damage after return may void coverage.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 text-light fw-bold mt-4">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p class="mb-0">
            To the extent permitted by law, Mod Labs’ liability is limited to the amount you paid for the specific service giving rise to the claim. Consoles are inherently at risk during advanced rework — you accept residual risk by proceeding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
